:"Bracebridge","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Bracebridge (Lincs)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":37,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":46,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William Bracebridge Baron Bracebridge of Tamworth was born in 1178, in Warwickshire, England, his father, Peter Bracebridge Baron Bracebridge of Tamworth, was 25 and his mother, Mrs. Peter Bracebridge, was 25. He married Baroness Amice de Arden in 1204, in Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1241, in Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1178–1241":"1178–1241","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1208–1277":"1208–1277","1153–1180":"1153–1180","1153–Female":"1153–Surnud","1204":"1204","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1277":"1277","1241":"1241","1153":"1153","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Kingsbury Hall, Ramwort, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tamworth, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","Kingsbury Hall, Tamworth, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1178–1241":"1178–1241","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1208–1277":"1208–1277","1153–1180":"1153–1180","1153–Female":"1153–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1277":"1277","1241":"1241","1153":"1153","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Kingsbury Hall, Ramwort, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tamworth, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","Kingsbury Hall, Tamworth, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, England"},"fr":{"1178–1241":"1178–1241","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","1208–1277":"1208–1277","1153–1180":"1153–1180","1153–Female":"1153–Décédée","1204":"1204","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1277":"1277","1241":"1241","1153":"1153","1185":"1185","1208":"1208","1180":"1180","Kingsbury Hall, Ramwort, Warwickshire, England":"Kingsbury, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Tamworth, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, A